# Product Hunt launch campaign: 4-week prep to #1-of-day

## Intent

Run a structured 4-week campaign that takes a shipping product to a top-3 Product Hunt launch, with measurable signup + revenue lift, then converts the spike into retained subscribers and audience.

## Scope

Run a structured 4-week campaign that takes a shipping product to a top-3 Product Hunt launch, with measurable signup + revenue lift, then converts the spike into retained subscribers and audience.

## Stages

### 1. Pre-launch checklist (T-4 weeks)

Pick the date, prep the assets.

Tasks:
- Reserve the launch date (avoid major collisions)
- Draft the listing copy + visuals
- Line up the maker bio + comments plan

Outputs:
- Launch date reserved
- Listing draft
- Maker assets

Decision gate: Advance only when listing draft is reviewed by 3 outsiders.

### 2. Audience warm-up (T-3 weeks)

Tell the people who already follow you.

Tasks:
- Send a save-the-date to newsletter and audience
- Run build-in-public posts that tease the launch
- Identify 20 hunters/upvoters likely to engage

Outputs:
- Save-the-date email
- Tease posts log
- Engagement target list

Decision gate: Advance only with >=20 confirmed early-supporters.

### 3. Hunter + maker DMs (T-2 weeks)

Pre-load the maker comments and supporter pings.

Tasks:
- DM 20-50 makers with a friendly heads-up
- Pre-write the first 5 maker comments
- Confirm hunter relationships

Outputs:
- DM log
- Pre-written comments
- Hunter confirmation

Decision gate: Advance only when DMs have answered yes I will engage.

### 4. Asset polish (T-1 week)

Make the listing un-skippable.

Tasks:
- Finalize images / gif / video
- Lock the tagline + first comment
- Test mobile previews

Outputs:
- Final assets
- Final tagline
- Mobile preview screenshots

Decision gate: Advance only when assets are locked >=24h before launch.

### 5. Launch day execution

Run the day with discipline.

Tasks:
- Post at the optimal hour
- Reply to every comment within minutes
- Push warm channels for upvotes (without begging)

Outputs:
- Launch post live
- Comment reply log
- Channel push log

Decision gate: Advance only when first 6 hours hit the target upvote pace.

### 6. Post-launch drip (T+1 week)

Convert the spike into customers.

Tasks:
- Send a thanks + onboarding drip to new signups
- Capture verbatim feedback from new users
- Push a recap post to all channels

Outputs:
- Drip sequence
- Verbatim feedback bank
- Recap post

Decision gate: Advance only when drip converts >=20% of new signups to active.

### 7. Lessons + #1-of-day post-mortem

Lock the learnings for the next launch.

Tasks:
- Compile the launch metrics
- Write a post-mortem with what to repeat
- Update the launch playbook with deltas

Outputs:
- Metrics report
- Post-mortem doc
- Updated playbook

Decision gate: Cycle closes when post-mortem is committed.

## Common pitfalls

- Skipping the decision-gate write-up to keep moving - closes the loop with vibes, not evidence.
- Treating each stages outputs as optional - every output is a gate input for the next stage.
- Letting one bad week stretch a fixed-cadence ritual into a quarterly one.

## Quality checklist

- Every stage has at least one referenced methodology that resolves under `knowledge/`.
- Every output is a real artefact, not a feeling.
- The final decision is a written commitment, not we will see.
